                           <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 80rab: በእንተ፡ አኰቴትነ፡ ናስተበቍዕ፡ ከመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ውስተ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ሕይወት፡ ስእለተነ፡ ይጸሐፍ፡ አምላክ፡ ይዝክረነ፡ በምዕራፈ፡ ቅዱሳን፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p part="N"/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Mädḫane ʿaläm is written on fol. 1v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a human: fol. 1v.&#xD;
- Encompassed writing on fols. 37ra, 38rb.&#xD;
- Erasures: e.g., fols. 24va, 63va.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: fols. 6rb, 23vb.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words are written interlineally: e.g., fols. 6rb, 13ra, 14va, 21vb, 35va.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections marked by thin lines above and below the words: fols. 14ra, 79va.&#xD;
- Lacunae (space for rubricated names left unfilled): e.g., fols. 48vb, 55vab, 56vab, 57rb, 58ra.&#xD;
- Pen trials: fol. 2r.&#xD;
- Scribbles and doodles: fols. 1v, 2r, 2v, 79v, 80r, 81r, 82r.</item>
                     </list>
